{"TopicId":144726,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Get an alert for science if you have a scientist on board","CreatedByName":"BT Industries","CreatedById":156823,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T07:27:18Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"BT Industries","CreatedById":156823,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T07:27:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/110827-abowl/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022110827\u0022 href=\u0022%7B___base_url___%7D/index.php?/profile/110827-abowl/\u0022 rel=\u0022external\u0022\u003E@abowl\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0had this amazing idea on his thread but due to a lack of explanation discussion on the topic stopped quickly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/144039-get-science-alerts-if-you-have-scientists-on-board/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIts really quite a simple idea in which you get notified if there is any\u00A0science around if you have a scientist on board.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this would be really useful and actually give me a good\u00A0reason\u00A0to carry Bob around in a craft that is to small for a lab.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat do you guys think\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-28T07:27:41Z\u0022 title=\u002207/28/2016 07:27  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 28, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by BT Industries\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"genericeventhandler","CreatedById":149557,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-28T08:56:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI use this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/95531-11x-automatedsciencesampler-v113-05052016/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;embedComment=1632162\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-1632162\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0 when you have a scientist on board, your science experiments goo / materials are reset. So most of the time I fly with a pilot, scientist and an engineer (with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003Ekis\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003Ekas\u003C/abbr\u003E and spare parachutes)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClicking and moving the scientist on eva around all the experiments was fun for the first couple of hundred hours play, but on my 4th career game it\u0027s become kind of tedious.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BT Industries","CreatedById":156823,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T02:56:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222694406\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144726\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469696160\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149557\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022genericeventhandler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/28/2016 at 6:56 PM, genericeventhandler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI use this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/95531-11x-automatedsciencesampler-v113-05052016/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;embedComment=1632162\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-1632162\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0 when you have a scientist on board, your science experiments goo / materials are reset. So most of the time I fly with a pilot, scientist and an engineer (with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003Ekis\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003Ekas\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E and spare parachutes)\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nClicking and moving the scientist on eva around all the experiments was fun for the first couple of hundred hours play, but on my 4th career game it\u0027s become kind of tedious.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds cool, still wish you could get a notification from your scientist and maybe he could automatically do the experiment if he is a level 4 scientist\u00A0or something along those lines\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"genericeventhandler","CreatedById":149557,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T10:57:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222696942\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144726\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469847387\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022156823\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022BT Industries\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, BT Industries said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds cool, still wish you could get a notification from your scientist and maybe he could automatically do the experiment if he is a level 4 scientist\u00A0or something along those lines\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nby the time you get scientists to level 4, most of the science will already have been done. \u00A0In all my career games I don\u0027t think one of them got more than level 3.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BT Industries","CreatedById":156823,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T11:04:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222697231\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144726\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469876234\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022149557\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022genericeventhandler\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, genericeventhandler said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nby the time you get scientists to level 4, most of the science will already have been done. \u00A0In all my career games I don\u0027t think one of them got more than level 3.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is a very good point...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe this would work\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLevel 1: science alerts\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLevel 2: automatic science collecting but for a low efficiency\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLevel 3: higher efficiency\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-07-30T11:04:48Z\u0022 title=\u002207/30/2016 11:04  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJuly 30, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by BT Industries\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Tex_NL","CreatedById":58254,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-07-30T11:07:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure if it still works but what you\u0027re looking for is \u003Cstrong\u003EScienceAlert\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/69538-104-sciencealert-189-experiment-availability-feedback-july-13/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fourfa","CreatedById":151713,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-08-02T06:00:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222697241\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022144726\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221469876828\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258254\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tex_NL\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/30/2016 at 4:07 AM, Tex_NL said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure if it still works but what you\u0027re looking for is \u003Cstrong\u003EScienceAlert\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/69538-104-sciencealert-189-experiment-availability-feedback-july-13/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nScienceAlert is the right answer to this question. \u00A0The author was/is working on it, slowly, in spare time. \u00A0Enough people got salty in the mod thread that it had to be locked. \u00A0Let\u0027s hope it comes back someday. \u00A0It definitely does not work in 1.1 unfortunately.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}